DIGEST
SB 84 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Myers
Present law provides for insurance coverage for prostate cancer screening for men over 50
years of age. Proposed law retains present law.
Present law provides for insurance coverage for prostate cancer screening for men over 40
years of age when it is medically necessary and appropriate. Proposed law changes this
provision to provide for coverage in accordance with guidelines from the National
Comprehensive Cancer Network and clarifies that it covers men between 40 and 49 years
of age.
Present law prohibits a health coverage plan from charging a deductible for any cancer
screening service provided for in present law.
Proposed law expands present law to prohibit a health coverage plan from charging any cost-
sharing amount for the services.
Effective upon signature of the governor or lapse of time for gubernatorial action.
(Amends R.S. 22:1028(B)(1) and (E))
